hopobject.body: Nice to meet you www.medicapanamericana.com/campbell Still, there's always more that can be done. More regular inspection to look for broken track may help reduce derailments. Separating train tracks from roads -- by building either bridges or tunnels where the two cross -- would do more to reduce vehicle-train collisions. And the faster implementation of devices to automatically stop trains if they run red signals could reduce train collisions.
